# LightRAG WebUI — build-time configuration template.
#
# Copy to `.env` (always loaded) or `.env.production` (only loaded for
# `bun run build`) before building, or pass on the command line:
#   VITE_API_PREFIX=/api/v1 VITE_WEBUI_PREFIX=/api/v1/webui/ bun run build
#
# These values are STATICALLY REPLACED into the bundle by Vite. They take
# effect at `bun run build` time, NOT at runtime — changing them on the
# Python server (or in a running container) does nothing unless you also
# rebuild the WebUI.

# Browser-visible URL prefix used as `axios.baseURL`, in `fetch()` template
# strings, and as the iframe `src` for the API docs page.
#
# Must equal the backend `LIGHTRAG_API_PREFIX` (the prefix the reverse proxy
# strips before forwarding to FastAPI). Empty / "/" → no prefix.
#
# Example: VITE_API_PREFIX=/api/v1
# VITE_API_PREFIX=

# Browser-visible URL prefix where the WebUI itself is served. Used by Vite
# as the `base` option (asset URL prefix in index.html) and by `<a>` links.
#
# Must equal LIGHTRAG_API_PREFIX + LIGHTRAG_WEBUI_PATH + "/" — i.e. the FULL
# path the user's browser sees, including any reverse-proxy prefix in front
# of the in-app mount path. Trailing "/" is required by Vite (it will warn
# and add one if missing); the normalization helper does this automatically.
#
# Example (WebUI at https://host/api/v1/webui/):
#   VITE_WEBUI_PREFIX=/api/v1/webui/
# VITE_WEBUI_PREFIX=
